descript.supplinf:
This USGS data release consists of an ArcGIS 10.8.1 geodatabase (USGS_TopoMineSymbols_ver10.gdb) containing six feature classes representing the different scales of topographic maps:

USGS_TopoMineSymbols_24k_Points;
USGS_TopoMineSymbols_48k_Points;
USGS_TopoMineSymbols_625k_Points;
USGS_TopoMineSymbols_24k_Polygons;
USGS_TopoMineSymbols_48k_Polygons;
USGS_TopoMineSymbols_625k_Polygons

No reconciliation between the data sets was done. Raster images of historic topographic maps may be obtained from the USGS topoView web mapping application: https://ngmdb.usgs.gov/topoview/.
